  "prompt": "How can I store 1TB of data online for free?",
  "response": "Storing 1TB of data online for free is challenging, as most free storage services offer limited space (typically 5GB to 15GB). However, there are a few strategies you can use to maximize free storage or achieve your goal:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Combine Multiple Free Storage Services**\n   - Use multiple cloud storage providers to collectively store 1TB of data. For example:\n     - Google Drive: 15GB free\n     - Microsoft OneDrive: 5GB free\n     - Dropbox: 2GB free (can increase with referrals)\n     - iCloud: 5GB free\n     - Mega: 20GB free (with bonuses for referrals)\n     - Box: 10GB free\n   - **Tip:** Create multiple accounts on each platform to increase storage, but ensure you comply with their terms of service.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Use Referrals and Bonuses**\n   - Some services, like Mega and Dropbox, offer additional free storage for referring friends or completing tasks.\n   - For example, Mega provides up to 20GB free and additional bonuses for referrals.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Leverage Educational or Organizational Accounts**\n   - If you\u2019re a student, teacher, or part of an organization, you may qualify for free or discounted storage.\n   - Example: Google Workspace for Education offers unlimited storage (varies by institution).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Use Backup Services with Free Trials**\n   - Some services like Backblaze or IDrive offer free trials or limited free plans.\n   - You can use the trial period to upload your data and then download it later.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Compress and Split Files**\n   - Compress your data into smaller files (e.g., ZIP or RAR) and split them across multiple accounts or services.\n   - **Tools:** Use software like WinRAR, 7-Zip, or PeaZip to split large files.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Explore Niche Cloud Services**\n   - Some lesser-known services may offer more free storage. However, research their reliability and security before using them.\n   - Examples: pCloud (up to 10GB free), MediaFire (up to 10GB free).\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Use Peer-to-Peer Storage**\n   - Platforms like [Storj](https://www.storj.io/) or [IPFS](https://ipfs.tech/) allow decentralized storage, though they may have learning curves.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Rotate Data Across Free Trials**\n   - Sign up for free trials of premium cloud services (e.g., Google One, Dropbox Plus), upload data, and download it before the trial ends.\n\n---\n\n### Important Considerations:\n   - **Security:** Encrypt your files before uploading to protect sensitive data.\n   - **Reliability:** Free services may delete your data if accounts are inactive or violate terms.\n   - **Legality:** Avoid violating the terms of service of any platform.\n\n---\n\nWhile storing 1TB for free is possible with these methods, it requires effort and may not be as convenient as paid storage. For long-term or reliable storage, consider affordable paid plans from providers like Google Drive, OneDrive, or Dropbox.",
